ANTHRAX - IRAQ (03): (NINEVEH) HUMAN
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 13 Sep 2021
Source: alwatannews.net/ [in Arabic, machine trans., edited]
https://bit.ly/3hwNB5s


A medical team in Nineveh Governorate, northern Iraq, deposited the stone after performing a surgical operation on a citizen, who later found out that he had anthrax.

The governor of Nineveh said in a press interview that "the initial diagnosis of one of the auditors was suffering from (appendicitis), where there is abdominal distension, but when a 2nd examination was conducted, it was proven to the contrary, and the tests showed that he had a hemorrhagic fever called (anthrax)."

He added that the competent (medical) cadres also quarantined his family members and all those who came into contact with him, and the veterinary departments were mobilized for the purpose of assessing the situation for fear of the presence of other cases.

The Ministry of Health had reassured citizens through Al-Mirbad after recording cases of anthrax in Dohuk governorate last August [2021], stressing that it is an endemic disease, and a few individual cases are recorded from it every year and is not epidemic, and it is a skin disease that is transmitted from animals to human.

