******
[2]
Date: Sun 12 Sep 2021
Source: alghadeertv.net [in Arabic, machine trans., edited]
http://alghadeertv.net/archives/32826


Today, [Sun 12 Sep 2021], Nineveh Governor, Najm al-Jubouri, revealed the details of a citizen's infection with anthrax in the city of Mosul. Al-Jubouri said in an interview with the official agency, "One of the auditors at a hospital in the city of Mosul, the initial diagnosis was that he had (appendicitis), where there is abdominal distension, but when conducting a 2nd examination, it was proven to the contrary, and the tests showed that he had hemorrhagic fever, which is called "anthrax".

He added, "All the health staff who performed the operation for the infected person, as well as his family members and all those who came into contact with him, were booked, and the veterinary departments were mobilized for the purpose of assessing the situation for fear of the presence of other cases."

He stressed that "the veterinary department has taken measures that would prevent and control the spread of this disease." He pointed out that "the area in which the patient lives have been monitored and all those close to him have been quarantined."

--
Communicated by:
Mahmoud Orabi
